column1: Information exposure through a stack trace
column2: Propagating stack trace information to an external user can unintentionally reveal implementation details that are useful to an attacker for developing a subsequent exploit.
column4: This information exposed to the user depends on [["stack trace information"|"relative:///index.js:16:12:16:14"]].

column2: An HTTP request handler that performs expensive operations without restricting the rate at which operations can be carried out is vulnerable to denial-of-service attacks.
column4: This route handler performs [["a database access"|"relative:///index.js:14:20:14:66"]], but is not rate-limited.
